The President strongly condemns the terrorist attack on a mosque in Chabahar, Iran. He describes it as a despicable offense and insists that those responsible be held accountable. The President emphasizes that acts of terrorism, like this one, do not recognize any religious, political, or national boundaries. The United States condemns all acts of terrorism and expresses solidarity with the families of the victims and the Iranian people. The President calls on people worldwide to condemn and oppose terrorism and support the universal right to live free from fear and violence.